<HEADLINE> Luneng Taishan Remains on Top of China League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Luneng Taishan remained on top of
the 14-team Chinese First Division soccer league after forcing a 1-
1 drew with Tianjin Taida in the 17th round match on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Luneng Taishan, took over the leading spot in last Sunday's
15th round, also became the first team ensured their berth for
next season's first division competition with a leading 32 points
from a win-drew-loss outcome of 9-5-3 after 17 of the total 26
rounds competition.
</P>
<P>
Luneng Taishan found themselves trailed 0-1 at the 29th minute
when the visiting Taida open the score with follow-up shot by Chi
Rongliang.
</P>
<P>
But Luneng Taishan tied it at 1-1 with a penalty goal with 17
minutes into the second half.
</P>
<P>
Luneng Taishan now is holding just one point leading margin
over second placers Liaoning Fushun, who trounced the bottom team
of Wuhan Heart A 5-2 in a road victory.
</P>
<P>
In the third position of the 14-team standings was Shanghai
Shenhua, who recover from their first loss of the season in last
Thursday's 2-1 defeat by Jilin Aodong and recorded a 3-1 win over
Chongqing Longxin at home on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Jilin Aodong kept unbeaten in last week's three matches
when they tied 1-1 with defending champions Dalian Wanda. The four-
time Chinese first division champions are still struggling at the
10th position with just 19 points on the standings after a winless
slow start at the first half of the season.
</P>
<P>
In other matches played on Sunday, Guangzhou Rongri ousted
Sichuan Quanxing 1-0 and Shenyang Haishi defeated Shenzhen Ping'an
2-1. Beijing Guo'an rallied from 2-0 behind to drew with Qingdao
Hainiu 2-2 on road. 
</P>
</TEXT>
