<HEADLINE> Davor Suker to Replace Anekla at Arsenal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Croatian striker Davor Suker is to
replace Arsenal's outgoing French striker Nicolas Anelka,
according to the club here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
With Anelka on the verge of signing with Real, ending three
months of transfer negotiations with other big European clubs
including Serie A teams Lazio and Juventus, Arsenal moved to buy
Suker from Real Madrid.
</P>
<P>
Suker, the leading goalscorer in the '98 World Cup, where he
lifted Croatia into the semifinals, is moving on a transfer worth
3.5 million pounds (about 5.64 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Suker became expendable at Real Madrid when he openly
criticized manager John Toshack. The 31-year-old striker has 41
goals in 49 international games. 
</P>
