<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Military Situation Worsens in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The military situation in
Southern Somalia is getting more complicated as the opposing
local factions, Ethiopian and Eritrean involvement are further
devastating the lives of thousands of nomads and farmers.
</P>
<P>
The latest reports from Lower Shabelle Region controlled by
Hussein Mohamed Aidid indicate that the town of Aw- Dhegleh, about
80 km south of the capital, Sunday night fell for the new armed
group called the Digil Salvation Army (DSA) fighting against
Hussein Aidid.
</P>
<P>
According to confirmed reports received through the VHF radios
in the neighboring villages and towns, Aw-Dhegleh district is
being run by the DSA forces and is reportedly quiet and calm.
</P>
<P>
The sources also said the shooting was heard in Barirreh
village and the towns of Qoryoley and Jannaleh in the region
controlled by forces loyal to Aidid.
</P>
<P>
Asad Abdi Mohamed, the spokesman of the DSA, also said that the
town has fallen for his forces early in Sunday evening. Mohamed
said his forces using battle wagons and infantry troops have
taken control of the town at about 7:00 PM Sunday night chasing
away the forces of Aidid.
</P>
<P>
There are no exact casualty figures available at this stage
since all communications have been either cut off or been put
under firm control by the DSA forces.
</P>
<P>
However, according to eyewitnesses who fled the fighting Sunday
night at least four people were killed and nearly ten others were
wounded during the fighting.
</P>
<P>
The DSA spokesman who briefly spoke with reporters in Mogadishu
 Monday said that his forces did not suffer any casualties.
</P>
<P>
In response to Sunday night's sudden attack on Aw-Dhegleh town,
Hussein Aidid's forces launched early Monday morning what could
be termed as a counter-attack against the DSA forces in Aw-Dhegleh
town.
</P>
<P>
Strong militia preparations have been visible in the streets of
the capital Monday for the reorganization of another
counter-attack operation against the DSA men in Aw-Dhegleh town.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, at least five people including a woman were killed
and 15 others were wounded after militiamen loyal to Muse Sudi
Yalahow have exchanged heavy gunfire with militiamen escorting a
lorry transporting commercial goods on the way from El-Ma'an
natural port to Mogadishu Monday.
</P>
<P>
The militiamen of Muse Sudi have reportedly erected a
checkpoint and tried to tax the lorries coming from El-Ma'an
port, an attempt refused by the militiamen escorting to
commercial convoys.  
</P>
</TEXT>
