<HEADLINE> Crime Gang Involved In Robberies In Macao Arrested In Southern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The public security department in
south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region has arrested 6
members of a gang suspected of involvement in the armed robbery of
a bank and casinos in Macao.
</P>
<P>
A preliminary police report said that the gang is accused of
four armed robberies between 1991 and 1994 in Macao with
submachine guns and pistols. They are believed to have robbed a
casino in the Hyatt Hotel, another casino in a major hotel, a
commercial bank, and a hotel, taking away money and casino chips
valued at over 40 million Hong Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
Macao police discovered that the people involved in the Hyatt
Hotel robbery were members of the Macao Mafia working with people
from the mainland and reported the case to the Zhuhai Public
Security Bureau in Guangdong Province in September, 1994. Zhuhai
police arrested two members of the gang. Then, this January,
police in Guangxi found evidence of the gang and by July 20 had
arrested another 6 members in Guangxi and Guangdong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
