<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> July Sees Robust Growth in SIMEX Trading Volume </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore International
Monetary Exchange (SIMEX) announced Monday that it registered a
double-digit percentage growth year-on-year in trading volume in
July 1999.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,275,615 contracts were traded in the month,
representing an increase of 18.1 percent compared with the
1,927,165 contracts traded in July 1998, it said.
</P>
<P>
The total trading volume for the first seven months of 1999 hit
15,606,513 contracts, amounting to a growth of 2.3 percent over
the 15,255,992 contracts traded in the same period last year, it
added.
</P>
<P>
SIMEX, formerly the Gold Exchange of Singapore (GES), changed
to its present name in 1983 to reflect its expanded role to
include financial futures trading. SIMEX began its business of
financial futures trading in 1984 and the financial futures market
in SIMEX features the system of mutual offset with the Chicago
Merchantile Exchange (CME) in the trading of Eurodollar and
Euroyen futures contracts. At the end of 1998, SIMEX listed 18
contracts, comprising 12 futures contracts and six options
contracts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
