<HEADLINE> Symposium To Mark Birthday Of General Zhang Xueliang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 2 (Xinhua) -- An academic symposium will be
held in Taian County, the birthplace of General Zhang Xueliang, in
northeast China's Liaoning Province to celebrate his 99th birthday.
</P>
<P>
The event is scheduled for August 6 to 8.
</P>
<P>
Zhang joined General Yang Hucheng in arresting Chiang Kai-shek
in the Xi'an Incident on December 12, 1936 to try and force him to
end the civil war and co-ordinate resistance with Communist forces
against the Japanese invasion. They released Chiang Kai-shek
unharmed after negotiations, but Zhang himself was imprisoned by
Chiang. Since the 1980s, Zhang has been living in the United
States.
</P>
<P>
The symposium is jointly sponsored by the provincial committee
of the People's Political Consultative Conference, the Zhang
Xueliang Foundation, and other organizations. It is expected to
attract scholars from China, the United States, Japan, the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea, Canada, and other countries.
More than 90 papers will be presented for the symposium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
