<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Promote Domestic Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia plans to provide
tax and monetary incentives for travel agents to promote domestic
tourism.
</P>
<P>
The decision on tax and monetary incentives which were given to
travel agents bringing in foreign tourists seven years ago to be
accorded to those handling domestic tourism as proposed by the
Malaysian Association of Tour and Travel Agents would be announced
soon, Culture, Arts and Tourism Minister Abdul Kadir Sheikh Fadzir
said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
This would encourage more locals to spend their vacations in
the country instead of going abroad, he said after chairing a
Malaysian Tourism Action Council (MTAC) Exco meeting, the
Malaysian national news agency Bernama reported.
</P>
<P>
The MTAC Exco was set up to enable the private sector to help
the government draw up policies towards boosting Malaysia's
tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
The minister said his government would launch the domestic
tourism campaign on a wide scale in conjunction with the launch
of the "Malaysia Fest" on September 11, to inculcate the culture
of holidaying locally among Malaysians.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia's domestic tourism had a market of 22 million people
and it would be a boon to this sector if they take vacations
locally, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
He also said the "Colors of Malaysia" procession would be held
on September 25 at the Merdeka Square (Independence Square) in
conjunction with the campaign to attract foreigners to visit
Malaysia. 
</P>
