<HEADLINE> Bangladesh National Table Tennis Championships Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The 23rd National Coca-Cola Table
Tennis Championships, organized by the Bangladesh Table Tennis
federation (BTTF), began here Monday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 190 players including 85 men, 14 women, 70 boys and
21 girls from 28 districts and organizations in the country are
taking part in different events of the week-long championships,
according to BTTF President and Defense Secretary Syed Yousuf
Hossain.
</P>
<P>
The tournament include team events, singles and doubles for men,
women and boys and girls. 
