<HEADLINE> Rebels Kill Four Philippine Cops in Ambush </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The New People's Army (PNA) rebels
of the Philippines ambushed a nine-man police team Monday and
killed four cops in Masbate province in the central Philippines, a
police report said.
</P>
<P>
The report also said that another policeman and two civilian
volunteers were wounded seriously in the firefight that lasted
about 30 minutes.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the police team was responding to a
report that the NPA rebels had gunned down a village captain when
they were fired upon by the heavily-armed rebels shortly before
noon.
</P>
<P>
The firefight resulted in a running gun battle after which the
rebels withdrew in different directions, dragging with them a
policeman in an attempt to use him as a shield.
</P>
<P>
The NPA has stepped up its fight against the government after
the Philippine Senate ratified the U.S.-Philippines Visiting
Forces Agreement in May.
</P>
<P>
The agreement allows the resumption of large-scale joint
military exercises between the U.S. and Philippine troops in the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
