<HEADLINE> India, Iran to Set up Working Groups </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- India and Iran have decided to
set up four working groups focusing on various aspects of the
ongoing dialogue between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
An External Affairs Ministry spokesman said Monday that the
decision was made during the two-day visit to Iran of Foreign
Secretary K. Raghunath, which concluded Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The ongoing dialogue between India and Iran will cover
political, economic, technical, strategic and regional issues like
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
It was agreed that these groups will meet regularly in New
Delhi and Tehran. 
