<HEADLINE> China's Working Class Urged To Take Lead In Criticizing Falun Gong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A Xinhua News Agency commentary "
The Working Class Should Stand in the Forefront of Criticizing
Falun Gong" today said that the nationwide political struggle
against Li Hongzhi and the Falun Gong should be led by the working
class.
</P>
<P>
It said that the People's Republic of China is a socialist
country led by the working class with a people's democratic
dictatorship that is based on an alliance of workers and peasants.
In China, the working class is the representative of advanced
productive forces and the fundamental dynamic force for social
stability, it said.
</P>
<P>
Li Hongzhi took advantage of people's desire to improve their
health to spread his fallacies and some workers followed him, it
said.
</P>
<P>
Since the founding of the new China in 1949, the life span of
the Chinese has been increasing because of improvements in social
conditions and the development of science and technology, it said,
so, to become good masters of their country, the working class
should believe in science and study science to distinguish between
truth and falsehood and to be the masters of their own fate.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that solving the Falun Gong problem as soon
as possible is in the basic interest of workers and that workers
should do a good job in their work and support the Communist Party
Central Committee's crackdown on Falun Gong and help maintain
social stability.  
</P>
</TEXT>
