<HEADLINE> Malaysian Business Delegation Visits Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A large Malaysian business
delegation held a seminar Monday with about 100 local businessmen
to study the investment environment and seek investment
opportunities in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
The delegation consisting of some 70 people was sent by
Malaysia's Ministry of International Trade and Industry.
</P>
<P>
The two sides exchanged views on investment prospects and
discussed the manufacturing, service and agriculture sectors.
Cambodia also tries to find a market in which it can sell
agriculture products.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for such a large Malaysian business
delegation to visit Cambodia after the new government was formed
last November.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia is the last leg of the Malaysian trade and investment
delegation in addition to Laos, Myanmar and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is considered as one of Cambodia's largest investors.
Its investments are in the areas of infrastructure, power
generation, tourism, banking, property, oil refining and
production, education and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will spend three days in Cambodia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
