<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chronology of Major Train Accidents in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- At least 500 people were feared
killed and over 1,000 injured in a train mishap in East India
early Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
This is one of the worst railway accidents in the country.
</P>
<P>
Following is a chronology of major train accidents in India
since 1988:
</P>
<P>
July 8, 1988: 107 people died as an express train plunged into
Ashtamudi Lake in the southwestern state of Kerala.
</P>
<P>
April 18, 1989: An express train derailed near Lalitpur in
North Uttar Pradesh, killing 75.
</P>
<P>
April 16, 1990: 70 people burnt alive as a shuttle train caught
fire near Patna, capital of the northeast Bihar state.
</P>
<P>
June 6, 1990: 36 people were killed in a collision at Gollaguda
in South Andhra Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
June 25, 1990: 60 were killed as a goods train rammed a
passenger train at Mangra in Daltongunj of Bihar.
</P>
<P>
October 10 1990: 40 died in a fire in a passenger train near
Cherlpalli in Andhra Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
October 31, 1991: 30 were killed as an express derailed near
Makaligurga in the South Karnataka state.
</P>
<P>
September 5, 1992: 41 died in a collision near Raigarh in
central Madhya Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
July 16, 1993: 60 perished in an accident in Darbhanga district
of Bihar.
</P>
<P>
September 21, 1993: 71 were killed as a passenger train
collided with a goods train near Chhabra in the northwest state of
Rajasthan.
</P>
<P>
May 3, 1994: 35 people died as an express train rammed a
tractor in Nalgonda district in Andhra Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
October 27, 1994: 30 were burnt alive when Bombay Mail caught
fire.
</P>
<P>
May 14, 1995: 52 died as an express collided with a goods train
near Salem of the southern state of Tamil Nadu.
</P>
<P>
June 1, 1995: 73 were killed in two accidents in West Bengal
and neighboring Orissa.
</P>
<P>
August 20, 1995: 302 people died as a Delhi-bound express
rammed a stationary train near Firozabad in North Uttar Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
April 18, 1996: 60 were killed as a passenger train rammed a
stationary goods train at Domingarh in Uttar Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
July 8, 1997: 33 died in a bomb blast on a passenger train at
Lehra Khanna railway station in northwest state of Punjab.
</P>
<P>
September 14, 1997: At least 81 were killed as five bogies of
an express plunged into a river in Bilaspur district of Madhya
Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
September 24, 1998: 20 people died and 33 were injured when a
train engine rammed a bus at an unmanned level-crossing in Andhra
Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
November 25, 1998: Some 200 people were killed and many injured
in the early hours when a south-bound express train rammed into
three derailed coaches near Khanna in Punjab. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990802.0086 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
