<HEADLINE> HK District Councils Electors Receive Polling Information </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 2 (Xinhua) -- More than 2.83 million
registered electors for the coming District Councils election in
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) are receiving a
notice of polling information, said a spokesman for the
Registration and Electoral Office (REO).
</P>
<P>
The notice details the electors' constituency and the
whereabouts of their designated polling station, enabling them to
know well in advance where to vote in the District Councils
election, which will be held on November 28, according to the
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The notices are being sent to electors in batches, inviting
them to indicate their language preference for election-related
communications with candidates, and the last batch will be mailed
by mid-August, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"If electors wish candidates to communicate with them in
English during the election, they should return the postage-paid
reply slip to the REO within 10 days of receipt of the notice.
Otherwise it is assumed that their preferred language is Chinese,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Electors' language preference will also be made known to
candidates, he said.
</P>
<P>
This arrangement was recommended by the Electoral Affairs
Commission in response to remarks made by some electors that most
candidates' publicity materials in the 1998 Legislative Council
election were printed only in Chinese.
</P>
<P>
A hotline is also set up by the REO for registered electors who
have inquiries about the notice.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a poll card, a map of the polling station, a
voting guide and an introductory leaflet on candidates of their
respective constituency will be mailed to electors around 10 days
before the polling day to remind them to vote.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
