<HEADLINE> Haze Covering Parts of Central Kalimantan, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Several parts of Indonesia's
Central Kalimantan province have been covered by haze since the
start of the dry season in early July, according to information
collected from the regions concerned.
</P>
<P>
The haze is posing an obstacle to traffic in towns as well as
in the countryside, the Antara News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Although the haze has not yet spread evenly, it is already
restricting the vision of motorists including drivers of public
transport.
</P>
<P>
It has been established that the haze has been caused by forest
fires started by locals in their efforts to clear land.
</P>
<P>
Local people have started to worry that they will soon undergo
a recurrence of the haze problems that hit Central Kalimantan a
few years ago when there was a complete breakdown of air and river
transportation.
</P>
<P>
A community leader in Central Kalimantan, Curnain Lambung,
called on local administrations to inspect the areas where the
forest fires have begun as soon as possible and take measures to
ensure that the fires do not spread.
</P>
<P>
But so far the local authorities have yet to do anything about
the problem although they already know the cause of the haze,
Curnain was quoted by Antara as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
