<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inflation Strips Zambian Farmers of Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The dwindling purchasing power and
rising costs have stripped Zambian farmers of most of the profits
in the production of pork, diary and poultry.
</P>
<P>
According to the annual report of Zambia National Farmers Union
(ZNFU) available Monday, farmers were unable to increase prices to
match the more than doubled costs of input due to declining
purchasing power on the local market.
</P>
<P>
Because of this dilemma, some farmers are leaving their
business, some small producers were forced to sell their farm
products on the street for somewhat higher profits.
</P>
<P>
The untested farm products has caused severe concerns for the
spreading of infectious diseases such as brucellosis and
tuberculosis in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
