<HEADLINE> Chinese Police Capture Roundup Escapees In Nationwide Raids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua)-- Chinese police, in the latest
campaign against criminals at large, have had some success, and
have rounded up more than 21,000 escapees since July 28.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Public Security said here today that more than
35,000 suspects have been caught since the campaign was started on
July 1 by the Committee of Political Science and Law under the CPC
Central Committee to eliminate hidden troubles and create a better
environment for the celebrations of the 50th anniversary of the
People's Republic and the return of Macao.
</P>
<P>
In order to improve the campaign's effectiveness, the Ministry
established an information network to provide detailed information
about suspects, directly provided by police units at various
levels. More than 2,000 information centers have been set up
across the country, where local police can visit the network. As a
result, more than 60 percent of the criminals caught during the
campaign have files on the network.  
</P>
