<HEADLINE> Arab Interior and Justice Ministers Hold Joint </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The joint committee of Arab
interior and justice ministers have agreed on the formation of a
mechanism for the implementation of the Arab agreement on
combating terrorism.
</P>
<P>
The committee held a meeting in Jedda, Saudi Arabia, Sunday
evening, the Saudi Press Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The joint committee comprises interior ministers of Jordan,
Algeria, Syria, Egypt and Yemen, and justice ministers of Saudi
Arabia, Syria, Iraq, Morocco and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The Arab ministers of interior and justice signed an
anti-terrorism agreement in April, 1998 to enhance inter-Arab
cooperation against terrorism. The agreement was enforced last May.
</P>
