<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Monday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 33.75
points to 734.94, the all-share Emas index fell 11.50 points to
188.03, the Industrial Index shed 47.70 points to 1,274.70 and the
Second Board Index lost 12.06 points to 155.56.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers 796 to 11 while 16 counters were unchanged
and 98 counters untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover increased to 538.558 million shares
valued at 1.063 billion ringgit (279.736 million U.S. dollars)
from 468.007 million shares valued at 1.155 billion ringgit
(303.947 million dollars) last Friday. 
</P>
