<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Hits Western Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 2 (Xinhua) -- A moderate earthquake measuring 4.3
on the Richter scale jolted Osaka Prefecture in western Japan
early Monday,the Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There was no report on casualties or damage and no tsunami or
tidal wave warning was issued.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake, which occurred at 4:58 a.m. (local
time), was estimated at 10 kilometers underground in southern
Osaka Prefecture, the agency said. 
</P>
