<HEADLINE> U.S. Embassy Re-opens in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, August 2 (Xinhua) -- U.S. embassy to Mozambique, closed
for security consideration on July 19, resumed operation Monday.
</P>
<P>
Harriet Macguire, cultural and press official at the embassy
said that the resumption of U.S. embassy operation is limited, as
the threats to the security of U.S. citizens and those visiting
the embassy are not yet over, their safety is still causing great
concerns.
</P>
<P>
A press statement from the U.S. embassy said that those who
want to visit the embassy's consulate, cultural section and other
departments can apply for appointment and those who want
information from the U.S. Information Service can be served
through fax, E-mail, telephone or other channels.
</P>
<P>
The embassy tightened its security measures after the embassy
bombings in Kenya and Tanzania last August.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Maputo embassy closed up after the United States'
foreign agencies including the embassy in Mozambique, allegedly
became the targets of threats in July.
</P>
<P>
The United States also closed its consulate, cultural section,
library and other offices in Mozambique on July 19.  
</P>
</TEXT>
