<DOCNO> XIE19990802.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Inflation Drops by 1.05 Percent in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia suffered a 1.05 percent
deflation or negative inflation in July, the country's fifth month
of deflation in a row, according to the Central Bureau of
Statistics (BPS).
</P>
<P>
The negative monthly inflation rate was primarily caused by a
stability in the prices of most basic food commodities, especially
rice, Chief of the BPS Sugito Suwito told reporters here Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said a 0.13 percent decline in the prices of processed
foods, beverages, cigarettes and tobacco, a 1.59 percent drop in
the prices of clothing and a 3.46 percent drop in the foodstuffs
had contributed to the deflation.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia posted a deflation of 0.18 percent in March, 0.68
percent in April, 0.28 percent in May and 0.34 percent in June.
</P>
<P>
The government earlier projected an inflation target of 17
percent for the current fiscal year ending March next year, but
recently revised it to 10 percent following positive development
in the country's macroeconomic picture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
