<HEADLINE> China Beginning Quality Education Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Communist Youth League of China (CYL) has begun a program to
develop survival and self-improvement skills and creativity among
young people.
</P>
<P>
CYL Central Committee officials say that the program was
designed to improve the physical and mental health of young people,
involving patriotism, moral standards, intellect, work technique,
and physical shape and it will build 100 centers for this purpose.
</P>
<P>
Also included in the training plan are 1,000 places to teach
special skills and techniques and a nationwide network of fitness
centers. Also planned is a series of centers to train instructors.
</P>
</TEXT>
