<HEADLINE> Thai Govt to Announce New Economic Package Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government will announce
a new economic stimulus package next week, focusing on tariff cuts
on imported raw materials to help reduce costs and boost exports
for local small and medium-sized enterprises, the Thai News Agency
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The announcement is expected on August 10, with tariff cuts on
imported raw materials believed to take effect immediately
following a cabinet approval, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The new package will also encourage venture capital and a new
national equity fund to help provide capital to small firms.
</P>
<P>
Measures to spur the property market and the tourism industry
will also be included in the package, it said. 
</P>
