<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Recapture Bagram Air Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's Taliban militia
Monday morning recaptured Bagram, 50 kilometers north of Kabul,
the only air base of the opposition forces, as the summer
offensive the militia launched entered the fifth day, news
reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The two warring sides were locked in an intense seesaw struggle
for the control of the air base located to the west of the
Panjsher Valley, the stronghold of the opposition forces.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban captured the Bagram air base Saturday night.
However, the forces loyal to former defense minister Ahmad Shah
Masood retook the strategic air base Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Independent sources said the total figure of casualties of the
two sides from five days of fighting was well in excess of 1,000.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban, which control nearly 90 percent of the war-torn
country, last Wednesday launched a major offensive to wipe out the
opposition forces with a view to extending their rule to the whole
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
