<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> At Least 500 Feared Killed in Indian Train Collision-PTI </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- At least 500 people were feared
killed and over 1,000 injured in a train collision in East India
early Monday morning, Press of Trust of India reported.
</P>
<P>
This is one of the worst railway accidents in the country.
</P>
<P>
Government Railway Police (GRP) sources said that the accident
occurred when Dehli-bound Bramhaputra Mail collided head-on with
Guwahati-bound Awadh-Assam Express shortly after midnight.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place near the west cabin of Gaisal railway
station, about 80 km from Siliguri towards Calcutta.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports had said the two trains were seriously damaged
by a big explosion.
</P>
<P>
Six compartments of the express train including one first class
and one air-conditioned coach, and eight bogies of the mail
including a general coach, were heavily damaged.
</P>
<P>
About 200 bodies had been already extricated by rescue
personnel from the mangled wreckage of the two trains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
