<HEADLINE> China's Arctic Expedition Getting Response From Publishers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SNOW DRAGON, August 2 (Xinhua)-- China's first government-
sponsored Arctic expedition will result in a number of scientific
publications on the North Pole, journalists aboard the expedition
ship predict.
</P>
<P>
More than ten publishing houses have shown an interest in the
expedition. Beijing's China Ocean Press was the first to ask for
materials from the expedition. It intends to publish books about
the history, scenery, environment, and flora and fauna of the
Arctic. And a publisher of works for children in Xi'an, in
northwest China's Shaanxi Province, is planning books on the North
Pole.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jinyou, of the State Oceanic Administration's polar research
office, says that a book of photos and reports of flora from the
Arctic expedition will be published.
</P>
<P>
Chinese reporters have caught the interest of the public with
their articles on the North Pole.  
</P>
