<DOCNO> XIE19990802.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Men Sentenced For Attempting To Subvert State Political Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 2 (Xinhua)-- Two men were sentenced today by
the Beijing No. 1 Intermediate People's Court for plotting to
subvert the state political power in November, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Zha Jianguo and Gao Hongming were sentenced to nine and eight
years in prison, respectively, and both were deprived of political
rights for two years.
</P>
<P>
The court found Zha and Gao collaborated with Xu Wenli, who was
sentenced earlier according to law, in plotting various ways to
subvert the state political power during November, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The court ruled that their behavior constituted a crime of
subverting the state political power and shall be punished in
accordance with Clause 1 of Article 105 of the Criminal Law of the
People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Members of Zha and Gao's families were present at the court
during the trial and the sentence.
</P>
<P>
Responding to the press, relevant Chinese officials say that
Chinese citizens' rights of freedom of association are protected
by law, however, organizing and plotting subversion of the state
political power violates China's Constitution and laws and shall
be punished according to law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
