<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990802.0182 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Afghan Fighting Raging in Northern Provinces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Fighting has been raging in
northern Afghan provinces of Kunduz and Samangan in recent days as
the dominant Taliban militia advanced in Parwan province abutting
on the capital Kabul, Afghan opposition sources said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Hussain Anwari, an opposition spokesman in Takhar province,
said the Taliban were using air support to push toward Takhar with
heavy fighting in the Khanabad district of Kunduz province.
</P>
<P>
Fighting was also continuing in the Dar-i-Safi district of
Samangan province, Anwari said.
</P>
<P>
He said eight Taliban fighters were killed and 10 wounded when
opposition forces ambushed a helicopter that landed close to the
front.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, thousands of people were fleeing their homes
in Parwan province Monday, the main battle area in which the
Taliban pressed its offensive against the northern-based
opposition forces, news reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The student militia have captured several strategic points like
Nejrab, Bagram and Charikar in their four-day long offensive in
the province, with hundreds of soldiers from both sides killed,
the reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
