<HEADLINE> Philippine Govt Suspends Work Due to Flooding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine national government
has suspended work in all government offices effective 3:00 p.m.
Monday due to widespread flooding and inclement weather in Metro
Manila.
</P>
<P>
Executive Secretary Ronaldo Zamora said in a memorandum
circular that the work suspension also applies to all
government-owned or -controlled corporations in the capital
region.
</P>
<P>
The circular, however, directed state agencies performing vital
functions to maintain a skeletal work force to ensure the
continuity in delivery of services and operations.
</P>
<P>
The circular added that all government services shall resume at
the start of the working hours Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the government assured residents of Metro Manila and
nearby provinces that it is closely coordinating with local
government units in assisting victims of Monday morning's flash
floods.
</P>
<P>
Secretary Orlando Mercado of the Department of National Defense
said the military has sent out trucks and rubber boats to assist
families affected by the floods.
</P>
<P>
He added that the National Disaster Coordinating Council, which
he also chairs, is keeping tabs on the situation in
lahar-threatened Pampanga Province near the capital region.
</P>
<P>
Flash floods caused by continuous heavy rains hit Metro Manila
and nearby provinces after midnight Sunday, killing 10 people,
including a family of seven in a landslide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
