<HEADLINE> Philippine Navy Searching For Missing Passenger in Ferry Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- Two Philippine navy vessels and
several pump boats continued their search Monday in sea waters off
Masbate, the central Philippines, for a passenger reported missing
two days ago after a ferry caught fire.
</P>
<P>
Reported as missing was Joseph Edoyan, one of the 210
passengers on M/V Rosalie II which caught fire four miles off
Cataingan, Masbate last Saturday, a navy spokesman said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The incident, which left three passengers dead, occurred hours
after the ferry left the central island of Cebu for Masbate.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that navy and coast guard ships rescued 206
passengers and the 28 crew members.
</P>
<P>
The ferry boat was only four miles from its destination in
Cataingan when a fire broke out in the engine room.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said two naval vessels -- the DF 317 and PG 377
-- have been scouring the sea waters between Basilay and Bugtong
off Masbate Island for the missing passenger.
</P>
<P>
Timely arrival of rescuers from the navy, Coast Guard and
fishermen prevented a high fatality rate, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Coast Guard has ordered an investigation into the incident.
 
</P>
