<HEADLINE> Death Toll Expected High in Indian Train Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 2 (Xinhua) -- At least 70 people were killed
and 135 injured in a big explosion that seriously damaged two
trains at Gaisan, 80 km from New Jalpaiguri early Monday morning,
PTI reported.
</P>
<P>
Government Railway Police (GRP) sources said that the mishap
took place when five coaches of Abodh-Assam Express and six of
Brahmaputra Mail met with a big explosion at Gaisan station.
</P>
<P>
The casualty figure was expected to be high, as the express and
the mail was passing by when the blast took place. The engine of
the express train was thrown away to the next down line under the
impact of the blast hitting the mail train.
</P>
<P>
Senior railway officials, police and local officials rushed to
the site. 
