- - - -
</P>
<P>
CANBERRA -- Despite a well-performed economy, Australians are
deeply concerned over the country's growing current account
deficit.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics released recently, Australia's current
account deficit in 1998-99 stood at around 22.44 billion U.S.
dollars compared with 15.51 billion U.S. dollars in the previous
financial year. The figure for 1996-97 was about 11.88 billion U.S.
dollars. (Australia-Economy)
</P>
