HARARE -- The Commercial Bank of Zimbabwe has raised 85 million
U.S. dollars from a number of international banks over the past
few months to support the country's exports and imports despite
the down rating Zimbabwe has received by most overseas banks, The
Sunday Mail reported.
</P>
<P>
The bank managing director, Gideon Gono, told the paper Saturday
that the export and import lines of credit are expected to boost
the country's foreign exchange position which has been negative
resulting in the substantial devaluation of the Zimbabwean dollar.
(Zimbabwe-Bank)
</P>
