<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Galliamova Ties with Xie Jun at World Chess Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAZAN, Russia, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Russian Alisa Galliamova
scored her first victory over Xie Jun of China at the third round
of the world women's chess championship here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Xie got off to a strong start but she was caught up at the 32nd
move by Galliamova who sealed the victory at the fortieth move,
tying Xie on 1.5 points from one win, one loss and one draw.
</P>
<P>
Chinese team captain Yao Wenyi said through the telephone that
the outcome of the match is no surprise considering the fact that
both players are on the same par.
</P>
<P>
"We only feel a little disappointed that Xie blew away such a
favorable situation and lost the match." added Yao.
</P>
<P>
The captain said that the chance for ties will become less
likely in the following rounds for both players are attack-minded.
</P>
<P>
The championship, which is shared by China and Russia, will
have its first eight rounds from July 29 to August 9 here and the
next eight rounds from August 13 to 25 at Shenyang, northeast
China.
</P>
<P>
As is regulated by the FIDE, the chess world governing body,
either player who first collected 8.5 points will be the winner
and a play-off is needed if both sides tie 8-all. 
</P>
</TEXT>
