<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Karrie Webb of Australia birdied
four of the last five holes in Calgary, Canada on Sunday to win
her first major LPGA title, capturing the du Maurier Classic by
two strokes over Britain's Laura Davies.
</P>
<P>
Davies made bogeys on the final two holes to surrender the lead
while Webb fired her second consecutive six-under par 66 thanks to
three birdies in a row starting at the 14th and a three-foot
birdie on the 18th.
</P>
<P>
The victory was worth 180,000 dollars to the LPGA money leader
and the 15th of her four-year LPGA career. Davies settled for a
second-place prize of 111,000 dollars from the 1.2 million-dollar
event.
