<HEADLINE> Davenport Defeats Venus Williams </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 1 (Xinhua) -- World number one American
Lindsay Davenport defeated fourth-ranked Venus Williams, her cocky
18-year-old compatriot 7-6 (7-1), 6-2 to win the Bank of the West
Classic on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, who won her second straight Bank of the West title.
</P>
<P>
Williams said: "I just made too many unforced errors at the
wrong times", "I didn't play as well. I feel I still have more
power than her but I had more unforced errors. She played well, I
played well. In the end, she was a little bit better."
</P>
<P>
Williams brought a 1-7 record against Davenport into the match
and promised to keep up with her bigger opponent from the forehand
side. Davenport has won the last four meetings.
</P>
<P>
Both players came out firing and played evenly until the
tiebreaker, engaging in fierce crosscourt rallies, eating up any
weak second serve and going down the line with authority whenever
necessary.
</P>
<P>
Davenport broke Williams to open the match, but Williams broke
back to 3-3 when Davenport mis-hit an inside-out forehand.
Williams held two sets points with Davenport serving at 4-5, but
the 1999 Wimbledon champion responded with a huge crosscourt
service winner and a service winner.
</P>
<P>
After that, Williams lost her focus. Davenport bore down and
played a consistent tiebreaker, while the Compton,California
native let fly four unforced errors.
</P>
<P>
In the second set, Williams had three break opportunities at 2-
4, but missed two return of serves and watched Davenport bang a
winner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
