<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, August 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Viktor Posuvalyuk
died in the early hours of Sunday at the age of 59 following a
protracted illness.
</P>
<P>
Posuvalyuk started diplomatic service in 1964 and worked in the
Soviet embassies in Yemen and Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Posuvalyuk headed the Foreign Ministry Africa and Middle East
Department in the last seven years of his diplomatic career. (
Russia-Diplomat-Death)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Russian Foreign Ministry Sunday condemned as "
absolutely unacceptable" the conduct of Kosovo Liberation Army
chiefs and remarks of Hashim Taqi, the KLA political leader.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said Taqi's remarks in connection with the
detention of the KLA chief of staff, Agim Ceku, was a "gross
provocation," the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Russian peacekeepers stopped a group of people wearing KLA
uniform in the town of Kijevo Saturday and Ceku was among the
group, the ministry's statement said.
</P>
<P>
The detained people were released upon being identified, the
statement said. (Russia-Kosovo)
</P>
