BAGHDAD -- Iraq on Sunday accused the U.S. and British
representatives in the U.N. Sanctions Committee of impeding its
transport contracts signed under the oil-for-food program.
</P>
<P>
Ahmed Murtadha Ahmed, Minister of Transport and Communications,
said in a statement carried by Iraqi News Agency that the
contracts concluded by his ministry are still on hold despite the
elapse of a long period since they were concluded. (Iraq-UN
Committee)
</P>
