<HEADLINE> Brazil, Mexico to Crash in Confederations Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Brazil will crash host Mexico
in Mexico City's Azteca Stadium on Wednesday in the final of the
eight-country Confederations Cup soccer tournament after the both
teams beat their respective rivals in the semi-final matches in
Guadalajara on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Reigning Cup champions Brazil secured a birth in the final with
an 8-2 rout over the surprising Saudi Arabia while Mexico defeated
the United States 1-0 in Extra time.
</P>
<P>
Brazil appeared to be coasting to victory with two goals in the
opening 11 minutes, from defender Joao Carlos and 19-year-old
Ronaldo Assis.
</P>
<P>
But Marzouk al Otaibi, the four-goal hero in the 5-1 victory
over Egypt, led a spirited first-half fightback by Saudi Arabia
with two goals in nine minutes.
</P>
<P>
Brazil retained its composure with a quick reply through Ze
Roberto two minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Three minutes later, in the 36th minute, Alex struck his third
goal of the tournament, heading in a cross from Ze Roberto.
</P>
<P>
As Guadalajara's Jalisco Stadium was struck by a second-half
torrential downpour, the Brazilian goal floodgates stayed opened.
</P>
<P>
Substitute Roni added a fifth goal, Ronaldinho, as the new
forward sensation is popularly known, sliding in for his second.
</P>
<P>
Alex then added his second before Ronaldinho fittingly
completed his hat-trick with a solo effort to close the Brazilian
scoring on the stroke of full-time.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Mexico took a sudden-death golden goal in Azteca
Stadium from striker Cuauhtemoc Blanco's at the seventh minute of
extra time to beat the United States in the day's other semi-final
match.
</P>
<P>
The Americans travel to Guadalajara to face the Saudis in the
match for the tournament's third-place spot on Tuesday. 
</P>
