<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sampras Beats Agassi at Mercedes-Benz Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Pete Sampras used a victory
over defending champion Andre Agassi in an all-American affair to
celebrate his return to the world number one spot on Sunday at the
350,000 U.S. dollars Mercedes-Benz Cup tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Sampras blended a solid ground game with a powerful
serve that produced 11 aces to power past top seed Agassi 7-6 (7-3)
, 7-6 (7-1) in the 95-minute showdown.
</P>
<P>
Sampras earned his 59th career title and the 46,000 U.S.
dollars winner's share to cap a brilliant week when the 12-time
Grand Slam champion ousted Australian Patrick Rafter to reclaim
the world number one ranking on the ATP Tour.
</P>
<P>
It ran his latest match winning streak to 17 including three
titles while improving his career edge to 15-10 over his longtime
rival.
</P>
<P>
Sampras officially was to take the number one ranking on Monday
when he would begin his record-setting 271st week on top,
eclipsing the mark Ivan Lendl held.
</P>
<P>
Though Agassi has won 17 of his last 19 matches including a
French Open crown, he has been denied twice by Sampras, in the
finals of Wimbledon Championships and Mercedes-Benz Cup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
