<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Australian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 2 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Australian newspapers Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian:
</P>
<P>
-- Republicans in Australia challenged Sunday Prime Minister
John Howard to join the republic debate.
</P>
<P>
The Canberra Times:
</P>
<P>
-- Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer refuted Sunday
reports of a rift between Australia and the United States over a
peace-keeping force in East Timor.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney Morning Herald:
</P>
<P>
-- Australian lamb producers Sunday began a one-month picket of
the U.S. embassy in Canberra expressing anger over U.S. lamb
import barriers.
</P>
<P>
The Age:
</P>
<P>
-- A barnacle-encrusted anchor found from under 35 meters of
water outside of Sydney Harbor is believed to be from the first
European fleet. 
</P>
